gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">There are two types of dumbbells. A fixed weight dumbbell and an adjustable dumbbell. A fixed weight is, as the name suggests, fixed at a single weight point. So, you would either be purchasing a 10 pound pair or a 20, 30, and so on. These types of dumbbells take up a lot more space and don’t give you a variety of options.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">While an adjustable dumbbell can be a singular piece of equipment that can switch between multiple different weight ranges. So, a single purchase can give a product that ranges from 10 pounds to 50. The switching of weight depends on the company. Some go with dial or switcher technologies, while others keep it simple and provide a clamp, similar to the one’s you’re used to using for barbells.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Adjustable dumbbells also come with their own storage tray. So, after you’re done using the equipment or even while using it, you can be in a mess free environment. Unlike fixed dumbbells, where you either have to buy a dumbbell rack or leave them scattered around.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802767" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1662136802767" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/5f2df6ea-18c6-42d1-a0e2-e85561c164a7/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Adjustable%20Dumbbell1.jpg" alt="Adjustable Dumbbell" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="800px" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802768" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802768"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3 Differences Within Adjustable Dumbbells</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802771" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802771" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>1. The design and the material used. The material used for an adjustable dumbbell can vary from simple steel and metal to rubber and plastic and everything in between. Each material provides its own benefits and concerns. Certain adjustable dumbbells also have an octagonal shape on their plates, while others have a longer handle, and some even have a box like weights attached to the dumbbell. These shapes can interfere with your lift, so you want to make sure you’re picking a dumbbell that allows you to perform all the exercises you need.&nbsp;</p><p>2. Not all adjustable dumbbells cover the same weight range or weight distribution. Some are more top heavy, so the weight of the dumbbell is closer to the ends of the handle. Others may have an equal distribution throughout the dumbbell. This is important to consider, especially if you plan on doing any explosive or athletic movements with the weight. As a shift in weight can cause you to lose your balance or make it harder to be stable.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>3. Lastly, the way you adjust the weight can vary ‌from one dumbbell to the next. Some are faster than others, some are more durable, and some are more complicated. The way you add or subtract weight can be a simple twisting method, where you physically twist the plate on or off the dumbbell. While others prefer a sliding pin method, which is typically smoother. So, if you’re into techniques like drop sets, pick a dumbbell that allows for quicker and efficient weight adjustment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802769" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802769"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Adjustable Dumbbell Benefits&nbsp;</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802770" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1662136802770"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Adjustable Dumbbells Are Cost-Effective</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802772" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802772" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Typically, a new dumbbell can cost anywhere from $1.50 to $4 per pound. So, just for a single 50 pound dumbbell, you could find yourself spending nearly $200. That also doesn’t include any storage space either. So, it’s just a matter of simple math.&nbsp;</p><p>If you want to have the capacity to workout using 10 pound dumbbells all the way to 90 pounds, you’re looking at a fortune. However, there are several adjustable dumbbell companies out there that can provide you with the weight range that you desire, while <a href="https://www.verywellfit.com/6-benefits-of-adjustable-dumbbells-5189687" class="" target="_blank">saving you a ton of money.&nbsp;</a></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802773" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1662136802773"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Adjustable Dumbbells Are More Convenient</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802774" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802774" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you buy a traditional dumbbell set for your home, that’s exactly where it’ll stay forever, your home. The most you can really do is take a couple of pairs with you if you wish to workout somewhere other than your home.</p><p>However, adjustable dumbbells are easy to transport. So, you have more options as to where you’d like to exercise.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802775" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1662136802775"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Adjustable Dumbbells Allow For More Variety</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802776" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802776" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Typically, if you’re looking to buy pairs of fixed weight dumbbells, you’re likely to skip out on the in-between weights, such as the 12.5 pound or 17.5 pound dumbbells. But, in order to make proper progress for certain muscle groups like arms and shoulders, you might need these weight options.</p><p>This is where adjustable dumbbells have a leg up on fixed weights, because they can go up in weight in 2.5 pound increments. Not only do you get more options, but you can then have more variety in your workout.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802782" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1662136802782"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Adjustable Dumbbells Are Space-Saving</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802777" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802777" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Again, you can either have 10 or more pairs of dumbbells laying around your room or you can have just one pair of dumbbells, taking up a small space in the corner of the room.&nbsp;</p><p>Adjustable dumbbells also come with their own storage tray, so you don’t have to worry about buying dumbbell racks or dealing with plates scattered around your room.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802780" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802780"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What To Look For In An Adjustable Dumbbell</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802784" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1662136802784"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Weight Range</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1662136802781" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1662136802781" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The weight range of adjustable dumbbells depends on the company. There are many adjustable dumbbells that cover weight ranges from 10 pounds to 50 pounds, but lack the additional weight to go heavier.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700129794873" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700129794873" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700129795021" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700129795021" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700129794897" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1700129794897"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-